  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators perform a case-control study to compare preparation before elective
      colorectal surgery. The first group is a prospective patient - registry in all patients with
      mechanical bowel preparation (MBP) and oral antibiotic prophylaxis the day before colorectal
      surgery. The second group is a historic collective of patients with MBP only and colorectal
      surgery. The cases were matches in American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) physical
      status classification system, BMI, operative procedure and risk factors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
